kdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3615808\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 09, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104scc1665702611448.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/scc1665702611448.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/scc1665702611448.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"scc1665702611448\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                              \n Background Image (BackImage)\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Image used as background for the application window, form, or entity. This property can be set in ProcScript.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"scc1665702611448__topic_d99323e1_d99324e1_d99325e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"scc1665702611448__p_d99326e1_d99327e1_d99328e1\">backimage\n                                 <code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">@FileName</var> | <var class=\"keyword varname\">^GlyphName</var>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"scc1665702611448__section_qtw_zjf_rwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1120660e66\">Usage</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"scc1665702611448__table_d11522e1_d11523e1_d11524e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Dynamic? </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Yes for entities, forms, and startup shells <p class=\"p\">No for\n                  area frames</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Supported in Grid? </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> No </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Dependencies: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> See <a class=\"xref\" href=\"#scc1665702611448__section_i2k_qkf_rwb\">Image Properties</a>. </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"scc1665702611448__section_dg1_2kf_rwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1120660e119\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"scc1665702611448__p_d99335e1_d99336e1_d99337e1\">The specified image can be a glyph or an image file on\n        the file system.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"scc1665702611448__p_d99338e1_d99339e1_d99340e1\">The <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Background Image</span> property is\n        dynamic and can be specified in ProcScript as BackImage using the following ProcScript\n        instructions:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"scc1665702611448__ul_fmy_fkf_rwb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"scc1665702611448__li_d40010e1_d40011e1_d40012e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bch1665702773514.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bch1665702773514.html\" title=\"Set or return the current window properties of a Form instance.\">$windowproperties</a>\n</code>—sets the background image for the form. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"scc1665702611448__li_d40013e1_d40014e1_d40015e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ifq1665702843454.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ifq1665702843454.html\" title=\"Set the presentation properties of the application shell.\">$applproperties</a>\n</code>—sets the background image for the application shell. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"scc1665702611448__li_d40016e1_d40017e1_d40018e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"tlm1665702687704.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tlm1665702687704.html\" title=\"Return or set the current representation properties of an entity.\">$entityproperties</a>\n</code>—sets the background image for an entity. </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"scc1665702611448__p_d99341e1_d99342e1_d99343e1\">You can also specify a default background image for\n        entities, application shells, and forms using the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">DEFENTITY</span>,\n          <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">SHELL</span>, and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">WINDOW</span> settings in the\n          <span class=\"ph filepath\">.ini</span> file.</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"scc1665702611448__ul_omy_fkf_rwb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"scc1665702611448__li_d40019e1_d40020e1_d40021e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"uvn1665702612860.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uvn1665702612860.html\" title=\"Logical widget for styling the default entity widget udefentity in Form components. The properties set are applied to all entities in the application. If DefEntity is not defined, the udefentity widget is transparent and follows Windows conventions.\">DefEntity</a>—for the default entity widget </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"scc1665702611448__li_d40022e1_d40023e1_d40024e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gma1665702671256.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gma1665702671256.html\" title=\"Sets the default window properties of the application shell.\">Shell</a>—for application shells, and forms </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"scc1665702611448__li_d40025e1_d40026e1_d40027e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"pqe1665702671325.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pqe1665702671325.html\" title=\"Set the default window properties for all Form components of the application.\">Window</a>—for form components </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"scc1665702611448__p_d99344e1_d99345e1_d99346e1\">Although it is possible to specify an absolute path to an\n        image, it is preferable to specify a relative path using the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">IMAGES</span>\n        initialization setting.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"scc1665702611448__note_vmy_fkf_rwb\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> The BackImage property replaces the imagewindow\n        property, which was not dynamic. Existing forms that have the image property set continue to\n        work, but if the <code class=\"ph codeph\">BackImage</code> property is set, it takes precedence over\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">image</code>.</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"scc1665702611448__section_wxn_kkf_rwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1120660e244\">Area Frames</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"scc1665702611448__p_d99350e1_d99351e1_d99352e1\">You can specify the background image for area frames\n        using entries in the [areaframes] section of the <span class=\"ph filepath\">.ini</span>. it is not\n        possible to do this in the Uniface IDE. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"sra1665702688552.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sra1665702688552.html\" title=\"The [areaframes] section of the initialization file contains logical widget definitions for frames in Form components.\">[areaframes]</a>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"scc1665702611448__section_z53_mkf_rwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1120660e263\">Combining Background Image and Color</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"scc1665702611448__p_d99356e1_d99357e1_d99358e1\">If both a background image and a background color are\n        specified, the background image may obscure the background color. Since it possible to\n        specify these properties in several places, you may get unexpected results. For example, if\n        a default background image is specified for form windows in the <span class=\"ph filepath\">.ini</span>\n        file:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"scc1665702611448__pre_tyx_nkf_rwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[APPLICATION]\nwindow=uwindow(backimage=^I_OK)</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"scc1665702611448__p_d99359e1_d99360e1_d99361e1\">and the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Background Color</span> is set in\n        ProcScript:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"scc1665702611448__pre_uyx_nkf_rwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">$windowproperties()=\"backcolor=blue\"</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"scc1665702611448__p_d99362e1_d99363e1_d99364e1\">the complete property setting becomes:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"scc1665702611448__pre_vyx_nkf_rwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">backimage=^I_OK;backcolor=blue</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"scc1665702611448__p_d99365e1_d99366e1_d99367e1\">In this case, the background color will not be\n        visible.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"scc1665702611448__section_i2k_qkf_rwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1120660e298\">Image Properties</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"scc1665702611448__p_d99368e1_d99369e1_d99370e1\">The following properties can be applied to the image\n        specified by <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Background Image</span>.</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"scc1665702611448__ul_em2_rkf_rwb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"scc1665702611448__li_d40028e1_d40029e1_d40030e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kmv1665702611521.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kmv1665702611521.html\" title=\"This property determines how the data (text or image) is aligned in the widget, entity, area frame, or window.\">Horizontal Alignment (Halign)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"scc1665702611448__li_d40031e1_d40032e1_d40033e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gvp1665702611605.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gvp1665702611605.html\" title=\"This property determines the vertical alignment of data (text or image) in the widget, entity, area frame, or window.\">Vertical Alignment ( Valign)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"scc1665702611448__li_d40034e1_d40035e1_d40036e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dbd1665702611680.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dbd1665702611680.html\" title=\"This property determines how the image is horizontally scaled; valid only for Image data types. Default value is 100 (percent).\">Horizontal Scaling ( Hscale)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"scc1665702611448__li_d40037e1_d40038e1_d40039e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"sup1665702611757.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sup1665702611757.html\" title=\"This property determines how the image is scaled vertically; valid only for Image data types. Default value is 100 (percent).\">Vertical Scaling ( Vscale)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"scc1665702611448__li_d40040e1_d40041e1_d40042e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yxe1665702611833.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yxe1665702611833.html\" title=\"Determines whether the aspect ratio of the image is preserved at all times. True (default) or False.\">Preserve Aspect Ratio ( PreserveAspect)</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"scc1665702611448__section_mfp_rkf_rwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1120660e381\">Applies To</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"scc1665702611448__ul_qfj_tkf_rwb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"scc1665702611448__li_d40043e1_d40044e1_d40045e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ula1665702613468.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ula1665702613468.html\" title=\"An Entity defines a logical data aggregation. It usually represents a relational database table, but it is possible to define non-database entities for transient data, reusable user interface controls, or other application structures.\">Entities</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"scc1665702611448__li_d40046e1_d40047e1_d40048e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"usl1704692305727.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/usl1704692305727.html\" title=\"Form components provide the user interface for Uniface desktop applications. They are always executed on the client system and can be modal (form retains focus until it is closed) or non-modal (users can switch focus to other forms).\">Forms</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"scc1665702611448__li_d40049e1_d40050e1_d40051e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ohj1705472401504.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ohj1705472401504.html\" title=\"An application shell is a module used to initialize and run an application (Windows or character-based) or application server.\">Application Shells</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"scc1665702611448__li_d40052e1_d40053e1_d40054e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ujj1665702610581.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ujj1665702610581.html\" title=\"Area frames are objects that can be used to group or separate the contents of a Form component.\">Area Frames and Lines</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3615808\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3615808\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Background Image (BackImage) Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 09, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Background Image (BackImage) Image used as background for the application window, form, or entity. This property can be set in ProcScript. backimage = @FileName | ^GlyphName Usage Dynamic? Yes for entities, forms, and startup shells No for area frames Supported in Grid? No Dependencies: See Image Properties . Description The specified image can be a glyph or an image file on the file system. The Background Image property is dynamic and can be specified in ProcScript as BackImage using the following ProcScript instructions: $windowproperties —sets the background image for the form. $applproperties —sets the background image for the application shell. $entityproperties —sets the background image for an entity. You can also specify a default background image for entities, application shells, and forms using the DEFENTITY , SHELL , and WINDOW settings in the .ini file. DefEntity —for the default entity widget Shell —for application shells, and forms Window —for form components Although it is possible to specify an absolute path to an image, it is preferable to specify a relative path using the IMAGES initialization setting. Note: The BackImage property replaces the imagewindow property, which was not dynamic. Existing forms that have the image property set continue to work, but if the BackImage property is set, it takes precedence over image . Area Frames You can specify the background image for area frames using entries in the [areaframes] section of the .ini . it is not possible to do this in the Uniface IDE. For more information, see [areaframes] . Combining Background Image and Color If both a background image and a background color are specified, the background image may obscure the background color. Since it possible to specify these properties in several places, you may get unexpected results. For example, if a default background image is specified for form windows in the .ini file: [APPLICATION] window=uwindow(backimage=^I_OK) Copy and the Background Color is set in ProcScript: $windowproperties()=\"backcolor=blue\" Copy the complete property setting becomes: backimage=^I_OK;backcolor=blue Copy In this case, the background color will not be visible. Image Properties The following properties can be applied to the image specified by Background Image . Horizontal Alignment (Halign) Vertical Alignment ( Valign) Horizontal Scaling ( Hscale) Vertical Scaling ( Vscale) Preserve Aspect Ratio ( PreserveAspect) Applies To Entities Forms Application Shells Area Frames and Lines Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}